{
  "stem": "25423.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Obviously, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we worked there-- there there were no Germans in this whole-- it was run by Jews and some Poles, so it was no problem.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were not paid anything, but we had what was called good papers, which allowed us not to be caught.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What you refer to as [NON-ENGLISH], Because it was vulgarly called as [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[GERMAN] in German means useful, [GERMAN], Jew-- a useful Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And even there was an aluminum plaque to that effect.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, I have it here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I don't have the placard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every Jew had to wear, under penalty of death, an arm band with the Star of David.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As much as I wanted to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not really the work-- we paid the Germans and the Poles for the papers, and we probably just were delivering symbolically some scraps here to elsewhere, which were collected by Jews whose livelihood this was before the war.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's very hard to answer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had to just simply, in a way, take care of yourself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The point is, that while in Lwow there was continuous pressure, continuous violence, and presence of Germans, and constant danger.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Rawa Ruska, they paid off the five or six German policemen, and the Ukrainian police was controlled by the Germans, who kept them in check.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, there was no violence when I arrived there for a few months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then the whole thing started there, too, but at a much lower pace.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All the time, because the post was functioning normally, and I got myself permits, which was rather unusual, to travel by railroad.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, I used to go to Lwow every two, three months to visit my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
